                },
                {
                    "text": " into groups of four for the project"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Common pattern: divide something into X parts/groups. Math context: 12 divided by 3 equals 4. Opposite: combine/unite."
        },
        {
            "word": "third",
            "wordType": "noun",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "One of "
                },
                {
                    "text": "three equal parts",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " of something; "
                },
                {
                    "text": "1/3 of a whole",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "ثلث",
            "synonyms": [
                "one-third",
                "33 percent"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "She drank a "
                },
                {
                    "text": "third",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " of the juice box before lunch"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Ordinal number (third place) vs. fraction (one third). As fraction: often 'a third' or 'one third'. Plural: thirds (two thirds of the cake)."
        },
        {
            "word": "dreamed of",
            "wordType": "verb phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To have "
                },
                {
                    "text": "strongly desired something",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " for a long time; to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "imagine achieving it",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "حلم بـ / تمنى",
            "synonyms": [
                "longed for",
                "wished for",
                "fantasized about"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "He's always "
                },
                {
                    "text": "dreamed of",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " becoming a pilot since he was a little boy"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Pattern: dream of + -ing verb OR dream of + noun. NOT 'dream to + verb'. Past tense: dreamed/dreamt (both correct)."
        },
        {
            "word": "exactly",
            "wordType": "adverb",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "In a "
                },
                {
                    "text": "precise or accurate way",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "; "
                },
                {
                    "text": "completely correct",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "بالضبط / تمامًا",
            "synonyms": [
